Ed,<br>
     That was beautiful.  Paul's right...What all of you guys are doing here on these threads is priceless!  What it is doing for each of you is obvious, but I sincerely doubt if anyone reading posts such as yours could not be deeply moved by the real-life love and tragedy of young men at war.  <br><br>
I find myself wishing that your words could have been written and read by all 30 years ago - the kind of understanding they evoke could possibly have prevented the ongoing tragedy of abandonment of our soldiers.  But never lose sight of what you're doing here to educate and protect present and future generations of young men and women.  Education and the power of discernment are our greatest weapons!<br><br>
&quot;If a nation expects to be ignorant and free, in a state of civilization, it expects what never was and never will be.&quot;   Thomas Jefferson<br><br>
Okay, you can come out of your room now.  I'll even let you stay up late and eat ice cream...I'd join you, but I'm on a diet?!?!<br><br>
